One of America’s largest unions is facing its own labor pains.
SEIU, the Service Employees International Union, represents nearly two million workers.
Yet staff at SEIU’s headquarters in Washington, D.C., could soon be going on strike.
Employees at SEIU are organized by two unions: the Union of Union Representatives and the Office and Professional Employees International Union.
